1
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:13,596
(Sound of Keisu)

2
00:00:22,647 --> 00:00:26,359
(Kotaro) It's like the world of Yokomizo Seishi.

3
00:00:27,193 --> 00:00:28,778
(Tatsumi) Yokomizoseishi?

4
00:00:30,739 --> 00:00:32,741
-(Tatsumi) Isn't he a shogi player? -(Torataro) Yeah, sorry.

5
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:34,659
- (Tatsumi) No, no... - (Torataro) I'm sorry, you can forget about it.

6
00:00:34,743 --> 00:00:37,287
(Kirie) That to Mr. Okayama's lawyer.

7
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:38,913
(Okayama) I was smart.

8
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:56,556
(Torataro) This is the will of the deceased... Tadayoshi Utsugi.

9
00:00:56,639 --> 00:00:59,350
(Kirieda) Yes, the probate procedures have been completed⸺

10
00:00:59,434 --> 00:01:02,437
Can this content really be considered a will?

11
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:03,730
(Torataro) Yeah?

12
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:07,358
I'll take a look

13
00:01:16,785 --> 00:01:19,579
Huh! ? This is...

14
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:25,752
Is the will a chess game?

15
00:01:27,962 --> 00:01:32,634
This is exactly the case for me.

16
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:35,136
♪～

17
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:47,357
～♪

18
00:01:48,525 --> 00:01:50,318
(Kasumi) Heritage division discussion?

19
00:01:50,401 --> 00:01:53,238
Yes, at the old house in Tamaicho⸺

20
00:01:53,321 --> 00:01:55,657
The head of the family passed away⸺

21
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:59,160
I received a request for procedures regarding inheritance.

22
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:00,703
(Tatsuo) Indeed, inheritance is...

23
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:04,499
There are many cases where problems arise when it's just relatives.

24
00:02:04,582 --> 00:02:08,878
I think asking a lawyer is the right thing to do...

25
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,839
(Kasumi) Why did you come to Kotaro-sensei's place?

26
00:02:10,922 --> 00:02:12,590
No, that's it⸺

27
00:02:12,674 --> 00:02:16,469
Suddenly, a request call came to my office.

28
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:20,765
I'm sure Tamai-cho is a place with hot springs.

29
00:02:20,849 --> 00:02:26,479
Yes, it seems quite difficult to take a day trip in the mountains.

30
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:30,024
This week, we will be together on Saturday with Ryumi Sensei⸺

31
00:02:30,108 --> 00:02:31,401
I'm thinking of going.

32
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:35,113
It's bound to be no good! My daughter before marriage went on a business trip...

33
00:02:35,196 --> 00:02:39,617
Division of inheritance is one of the great duties of a lawyer!

34
00:02:40,201 --> 00:02:43,538
As it is a business, we will proceed with caution.

35
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:46,040
Sounds good?

36
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:50,253
I admit

37
00:02:51,462 --> 00:02:54,424
What is Tsume Shogi...

38
00:02:55,049 --> 00:02:58,595
Ah, Tsume Shogi is a type of puzzle using Shogi.

39
00:02:58,678 --> 00:03:01,598
The first player continues to make moves within the set number of moves⸺

40
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:03,725
You must block the opponent's balls.

41
00:03:03,808 --> 00:03:05,560
Was there anything else?

42
00:03:05,643 --> 00:03:07,353
No, what was in the safe was⸺

43
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:08,813
There was only that one letter.

44
00:03:08,897 --> 00:03:10,857
 (Matsuhiko) No matter how much he is a shogi fanatic,

45
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:13,651
How can you leave such a ridiculous will?

46
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:15,778
There is a limit to making fun of people

47
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:17,447
Do you hate shogi?

48
00:03:17,530 --> 00:03:20,325
 (Shiko) My father was the only person in this house who liked shogi.

49
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:21,492
Everyone else is playing shogi⸺

50
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:22,827
I hated it.

51
00:03:22,911 --> 00:03:24,913
 (Sugio)...I mean, that's what it is.

52
00:03:24,996 --> 00:03:27,248
It has no effect as a will.

53
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:29,792
(Tatsumi) Ah, no, in this will⸺

54
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:33,880
Date and testator Tadayoshi Utsugi⸺

55
00:03:33,963 --> 00:03:36,883
The name is written and the seal is affixed.

56
00:03:36,966 --> 00:03:38,676
If it is in your own handwriting⸺

57
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:42,263
The conditions for a handwritten will are met.

58
00:03:42,347 --> 00:03:44,557
 Above all, in the margin⸺

59
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:47,477
For everyone that is not found in ordinary Tsume Shogi⸺

60
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:48,937
I have a name

61
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:53,691
(Shiko) It's true, my sister is the rook and I'm the money.

62
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:56,152
Am I silver?

63
00:03:56,235 --> 00:03:59,864
(Okayama) Me and Shiori's names are also there.

64
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:03,409
(Torataro) Yes, I am sure that the butler, Mr. Okayama⸺

65
00:04:03,493 --> 00:04:05,745
Two more names

66
00:04:05,828 --> 00:04:07,455
 (Shiori) I passed away⸺

67
00:04:07,538 --> 00:04:11,918
She is the daughter of Chairman Utsugi's niece, and her name is Makino Shiori.

68
00:04:12,001 --> 00:04:15,546
I have been working at Utsugi Kenzai for many years...

69
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:17,924
Oh, this is my son Yuuma.

70
00:04:18,007 --> 00:04:19,300
(Okayama) Um...

71
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:22,595
Having a name means heritage⸺

72
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:25,473
Does that mean you can share it?

73
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:28,851
Not only me, but also Shiori-sama.

74
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:32,271
No, the inheritance I can receive...

75
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:33,773
In this house with Yuma⸺

76
00:04:33,856 --> 00:04:35,817
It's enough just to let me live there.

77
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:38,945
(Matsuhiko) In other words, a will like this would be invalid.

78
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:42,615
Isn't it a good idea to divide one-fourth among the four siblings?

79
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:43,700
- (Shiko) Let's do that - (Sugio) That's right.

80
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:44,659
(Shiko) 1/4

81
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:47,203
-(Sugio) 1 2 3 4... -(Tatsumi) Please wait!

82
00:04:47,286 --> 00:04:51,332
It has not yet been determined that this will is invalid.

83
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:55,378
There is a possibility that a message from the deceased may be hidden in this⸺

84
00:04:56,004 --> 00:04:59,674
The inheritance will be divided after solving this chess game.

85
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:06,139
Yeah? Isn't it because you want to solve it?

86
00:05:06,222 --> 00:05:08,433
Can I borrow a shogi board?

87
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:12,145
It's a large mansion

88
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,898
Amazing, there's even a floor plan

89
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:17,483
(Torataro) Wow!

90
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:20,570
Come to think of it, why did you ask our office?

91
00:05:20,653 --> 00:05:25,283
Ah, a lawyer I know has filed various lawsuits.

92
00:05:25,366 --> 00:05:28,244
For some reason, I solved the problem by relating it to shogi⸺

93
00:05:28,327 --> 00:05:31,247
I heard that there is a teacher who is knowledgeable about shogi.

94
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:34,751
Become famous before you know it

95
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:39,630
Ah, um... Kirie-san also plays shogi...

96
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:42,884
I don't like it

97
00:05:46,387 --> 00:05:49,599
(Torataro) Why do you all hate shogi?

98
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:52,894
It's all my father's fault

99
00:05:54,103 --> 00:05:56,147
My mother who passed away was often sick⸺

100
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:58,316
I was repeatedly in and out of the hospital.

101
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:00,735
Because of that, my father...

102
00:06:00,818 --> 00:06:03,654
He took care of the four of us when we were young.

103
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:06,949
Oh, aren't you a good father?

104
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:10,536
My father is⸺

105
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:13,081
Shogi was my only hobby⸺

106
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:16,375
They tried to force it on us.

107
00:06:20,588 --> 00:06:25,384
 (Loyalty) This is the end. Kirie. Read further.

108
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:31,140
If I lose, I'll definitely say "I'm here"

109
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:33,226
(Junior high school student Kirie) It's boring if you can't win!

110
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:36,062
If that happens, you'll never be able to become stronger!

111
00:06:37,396 --> 00:06:40,817
(Kirieda) He just teaches children harshly...

112
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:46,072
That's why everyone started hating shogi.

113
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:51,702
10 years ago Even after retiring from work⸺

114
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:56,416
I live a life full of shogi, traveling around Japan as I please.

115
00:06:57,708 --> 00:07:01,712
Then last month, I suddenly collapsed...

116
00:07:05,299 --> 00:07:08,636
After causing so much trouble to our family⸺

117
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:11,973
In his final moments, he died alone.

118
00:07:14,308 --> 00:07:16,561
This is my father's study.

119
00:07:16,644 --> 00:07:20,690
There are also shogi tools inside, so please feel free to use them.

120
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:22,150
(Tatsumi/Torataro) Thank you

121
00:07:26,487 --> 00:07:29,073
(Torataro) What do you think? Do you think you can solve it?

122
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:31,117
It's quite a difficult question

123
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:36,372
Is there really a hidden message in this Tsume Shogi?

124
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:41,544
The fact that I purposely specified the 25th move is⸺

125
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:45,298
Maybe it's guiding you to a specific shape of blockage.

126
00:07:45,798 --> 00:07:47,175
What I'm curious about is⸺

127
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:50,178
That's the name of the person in this house on the margin.

128
00:07:54,056 --> 00:07:56,684
-(Torataro) Ah-(Tatsumi) Huh...

129
00:07:58,269 --> 00:07:59,687
It's a jam, right?

130
00:08:01,272 --> 00:08:02,982
It'll come out in a little while

131
00:08:03,065 --> 00:08:04,734
- (Tatsumi) Yes - (Torataro) Yeah.

132
00:08:04,817 --> 00:08:08,070
(sound of sliding door opening and closing)

133
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:11,032
(sound of cutting branches)

134
00:08:11,115 --> 00:08:12,909
(Torataro)…This house is spacious.

135
00:08:12,992 --> 00:08:17,038
Ah, the tree care is really sloppy.

136
00:08:17,121 --> 00:08:19,248
Looks like my father's house

137
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:21,834
Hey, listen to me

138
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:24,962
-(Torataro) Ah, ah... -(Shiko) You're so sloppy.

139
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:26,088
yes

140
00:08:26,714 --> 00:08:29,717
Ah, I'm sure Shiiko-san...

141
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:33,429
I am the representative of an NPO that engages in forest protection activities.

142
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:36,849
Ah, my late father is from the sawmill⸺

143
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:40,561
You founded Utsugi Kenzai and served as chairman.

144
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:45,024
(Shiko) When my father started a sawmill, all you had to do was cut as much wood as you could.

145
00:08:45,107 --> 00:08:49,529
There was no idea that trees and humans could coexist.

146
00:08:50,029 --> 00:08:54,492
Perhaps that reaction led to my current NPO activities...

147
00:08:55,284 --> 00:08:59,956
(Shiko) If you understand, please share a lot of your inheritance with me.

148
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:01,165
yes?

149
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:04,710
The answer to that Tsume Shogi game is more than 1/4⸺

150
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:07,338
Could you please do what I said I would give you a lot?

151
00:09:07,421 --> 00:09:10,549
It's obvious that the other three people won't be able to use it properly.

152
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:13,386
So please give me the largest inheritance!

153
00:09:13,469 --> 00:09:14,804
Please stop it.

154
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:16,681
Shiiko Shiiko! Stop it, you!

155
00:09:16,764 --> 00:09:19,433
- (Torataro) Ah... Ah, good - (Matsuhiko) What are you doing?

156
00:09:19,517 --> 00:09:21,477
(Torataro) Good, Matsuhiko-san.

157
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:24,230
If I were to divide the majority of my inheritance, of course it would be me.

158
00:09:24,313 --> 00:09:25,523
ah?

159
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:28,985
I'm not bragging, but the quality of our furniture manufacturer is good.

160
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:32,822
However, sales have been sluggish in recent years.

161
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:33,864
ask

162
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:37,034
(Shiko) You can't do that. If you're going to spend a lot of money, please do it to me.

163
00:09:37,118 --> 00:09:39,996
At least half? Just like this!

164
00:09:40,788 --> 00:09:43,249
Just a moment...both of you calm down.

165
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:47,044
(Matsuhiko) Haa, is it okay to say such carefree things?

166
00:09:47,128 --> 00:09:49,714
While I was doing this, my younger brother Sugio...

167
00:09:49,797 --> 00:09:53,050
Maybe he's trying to trick her into it.

168
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:57,263
She... no, only Ryumi-sensei is like that...

169
00:09:57,346 --> 00:09:58,806
Before opening Sugio's restaurant⸺

170
00:09:58,889 --> 00:10:00,766
There are even rumors that he was the host⸺

171
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:02,560
I might not be able to let my guard down

172
00:10:09,483 --> 00:10:11,402
(Matsuhiko) Hey, you, that's a little... lower it, you, that.

173
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:12,486
(Shiko) I don't like it.

174
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:21,120
(Sugio) In Ryumi-chan's Tsume Shogi game, I won silver.

175
00:10:22,246 --> 00:10:25,041
So silver is the strongest?

176
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:28,377
I answered as if I had the biggest share⸺

177
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:31,964
Can you give it to me?

178
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:38,638
As the saying goes, “Silver is an attack, and gold is a receiver”⸺

179
00:10:38,721 --> 00:10:41,432
Silver is by no means the strongest piece.

180
00:10:41,515 --> 00:10:42,350
(sound of sliding door opening)

181
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:45,144
a little bit! What are you doing! ?

182
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:48,189
Even if we bring our lawyers to tears⸺

183
00:10:48,272 --> 00:10:49,774
You cannot change the contents of a will!

184
00:10:49,857 --> 00:10:52,860
Tatata... please, okay? If it stays like this⸺

185
00:10:52,943 --> 00:10:55,363
The store that I worked so hard to open is now in the hands of someone else.

186
00:10:55,446 --> 00:10:56,822
(mobile phone vibrator)

187
00:10:56,906 --> 00:11:00,284
Oh no...

188
00:11:01,577 --> 00:11:04,455
Yes, sorry, I'll return it right away!

189
00:11:04,538 --> 00:11:08,542
Yes, what now? Ah, okay, I understand. I'll go right away!

190
00:11:10,127 --> 00:11:15,383
What on earth are these people in this house like...ha...

191
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:17,343
(Yuma) Amazing! I'm solving Tsume Shogi

192
00:11:17,426 --> 00:11:19,970
Ah, no, that doesn't mean it's solved yet...

193
00:11:20,054 --> 00:11:22,348
If so, come here and I'll show you a hint.

194
00:11:22,431 --> 00:11:24,058
Oh, wait a minute...

195
00:11:24,141 --> 00:11:25,768
- (Yuma) Here, here - (Tatsumi) Huh?

196
00:11:26,811 --> 00:11:31,941
(Torataro) Wow... Wow, there's even a storehouse like this!

197
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:35,069
It's my loyal grandpa's and my secret base.

198
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:38,656
Hey, wow...

199
00:11:38,739 --> 00:11:42,201
Looks like something will come out

200
00:11:42,284 --> 00:11:43,828
What does it mean to come out?

201
00:11:43,911 --> 00:11:47,415
(Torataro) Speaking from Yokomizo, ghosts of demobilized soldiers and fallen warriors...

202
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:48,541
-(Tatsumi) Ah! -(Torataro) Wow!

203
00:11:48,624 --> 00:11:50,668
What?

204
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:51,961
It's a shogi board

205
00:11:52,044 --> 00:11:55,506
Wow~ The pieces too, huh?

206
00:11:56,882 --> 00:11:58,509
Chess match flyer

207
00:11:59,593 --> 00:12:00,928
Wow~

208
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:06,058
Ah, the fact that he was flying around all over Japan⸺

209
00:12:06,142 --> 00:12:10,146
You were chasing a local title match.

210
00:12:11,021 --> 00:12:14,567
I really lived a life full of shogi.

211
00:12:15,359 --> 00:12:16,193
(Yuma) Let's play shogi

212
00:12:16,277 --> 00:12:19,447
Eh, oh, ah, I can play shogi.

213
00:12:19,530 --> 00:12:21,991
Yeah, but why me?

214
00:12:22,074 --> 00:12:24,368
Because the older brother seems weaker

215
00:12:25,077 --> 00:12:28,205
(Torataro) Hoho, let's do it.

216
00:12:28,789 --> 00:12:30,708
Okay

217
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:36,964
Huh? here

218
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:43,471
(Torataro) Hmm, I guess this is it.

219
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:47,725
Yeah? This is...

220
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:50,060
(Torataro) Here we come.

221
00:12:50,144 --> 00:12:51,479
Huh? Already?

222
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:54,190
No, I lost

223
00:12:55,357 --> 00:13:00,154
Oh, that's a great loss.

224
00:13:00,237 --> 00:13:04,408
No, this won't work unless the losing side also makes some bad moves.

225
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:07,995
In a sense, Kotaro-sensei is also brilliant.

226
00:13:09,205 --> 00:13:12,041
I don't feel like I'm being praised though.

227
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:14,126
Yuma-kun, you're strong, aren't you?

228
00:13:14,210 --> 00:13:16,545
I'm training with a shogi app.

229
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:18,589
It's not these days.

230
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,762
Ah, what do you think? Did you find any tips for Tsume Shogi?

231
00:13:24,845 --> 00:13:27,765
(Tatsumi) Ah, no, I don't know if this is a hint or not...

232
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:32,269
(Torataro) Is this Chairman Utsugi's wife?

233
00:13:32,353 --> 00:13:35,189
I heard that he passed away from an illness about 30 years ago.

234
00:13:35,272 --> 00:13:38,859
I think the four children are Kirie-san and his siblings.

235
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:41,403
Ah, even in this house⸺

236
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:44,615
I guess he had time to play shogi so happily.

237
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:47,660
(Tatsumi) I can't believe that's gone now.

238
00:13:47,743 --> 00:13:50,204
I feel sorry for Shogi somehow.

239
00:13:51,205 --> 00:13:53,541
Do you feel sorry for Shogi?

240
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:57,920
It seems like everyone in this house is unhappy because of shogi.

241
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:02,132
It's kind of sad

242
00:14:02,841 --> 00:14:03,926
(Torataro) Yeah.

243
00:14:06,136 --> 00:14:11,559
I don't want to see anyone get hurt playing shogi again.

244
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:16,647
That’s it⸺

245
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:19,567
