 (Okayama) “The 25th move is⸺”

493
00:31:04,779 --> 00:31:08,199
It says “94 rooks”

494
00:31:09,492 --> 00:31:11,119
Is this okay?

495
00:31:11,202 --> 00:31:16,583
If the pieces match, it is the same dragon, so the draw is 7 triples.

496
00:31:16,666 --> 00:31:18,960
(Sugio) Okay, one more move then?

497
00:31:19,043 --> 00:31:20,795
The last move is⸺

498
00:31:21,921 --> 00:31:25,091
Thank you to Kirie-san.

499
00:31:26,301 --> 00:31:27,510
Huh?

500
00:31:33,433 --> 00:31:34,309
Ah

501
00:31:48,698 --> 00:31:52,368
Even the incense car would get stuck, but if it were me...

502
00:31:54,370 --> 00:31:55,663
This way

503
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:57,290
(Yuma) 8 three dragons!

504
00:31:59,083 --> 00:32:00,251
(Loyalty) This is the end.

505
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:03,171
If I lose, I'll definitely say "I'm here"

506
00:32:05,006 --> 00:32:08,384
Dad has arrived

507
00:32:20,730 --> 00:32:22,231
congratulations

508
00:32:23,191 --> 00:32:27,362
I got stuck on the 27th move.

509
00:32:27,445 --> 00:32:28,863
-(Sugio) Oh!-(Yuma) Yay!

510
00:32:28,946 --> 00:32:30,281
-(Sugio) Seriously?-(Shiko) Does that mean it's solved?

511
00:32:30,365 --> 00:32:33,034
(Matsuhiko) Well, it's been a while since I used my brain.

512
00:32:33,117 --> 00:32:34,869
(Okayama) Hahahaha…

513
00:32:34,952 --> 00:32:40,333
I believe this final diagram contains the wishes of the deceased.

514
00:32:40,416 --> 00:32:42,210
Chairman Utsugi's last will?

515
00:32:42,293 --> 00:32:46,214
(Tatsumi) Yes, this is a message from Tadayoshi Utsugi.

516
00:32:47,674 --> 00:32:53,304
There are now 8 pieces left on the board.

517
00:32:55,306 --> 00:33:00,812
When you connect the pieces other than the last dragon you put your hand on⸺

518
00:33:02,438 --> 00:33:06,567
Don't you notice that it looks similar to something you've seen somewhere before?

519
00:33:06,651 --> 00:33:12,031
(Shiko) The balance is poor for an inverted T.

520
00:33:12,115 --> 00:33:13,908
Is the katakana letter lying down?

521
00:33:13,991 --> 00:33:16,786
Oh wait! This is⸺

522
00:33:16,869 --> 00:33:19,539
Maybe it's the shape of this house?

523
00:33:19,622 --> 00:33:20,832
yes

524
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:28,339
It resembled the floor plan of this mansion in the hallway.

525
00:33:29,424 --> 00:33:32,301
Sorry, I brought it without permission.

526
00:33:32,385 --> 00:33:35,221
(Tatsumi) This Tsume Shogi is for classic Tsume Shogi⸺

527
00:33:35,304 --> 00:33:39,017
There were multiple ways to escape from the blockage⸺

528
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:41,769
In all filling diagrams including this shape⸺

529
00:33:41,853 --> 00:33:42,687
In a common position⸺

530
00:33:42,770 --> 00:33:44,564
Existing piece found

531
00:33:44,647 --> 00:33:50,695
That is the 21st Katsura and the 11th Incense.

532
00:33:50,778 --> 00:33:52,488
These two pieces are⸺

533
00:33:53,281 --> 00:33:55,658
From the positional relationship with this mansion⸺

534
00:33:55,742 --> 00:33:59,287
It seems to indicate a storehouse in the garden.

535
00:33:59,370 --> 00:34:04,792
(Tatsumi) Using this Tsume Shogi to point out that storehouse⸺

536
00:34:04,876 --> 00:34:07,754
It was the deceased's first message.

537
00:34:14,927 --> 00:34:19,056
Mr. Tadayoshi, who was a shogi enthusiast, works in this warehouse.

538
00:34:19,140 --> 00:34:22,977
Items purchased from all over the country are carefully stored.

539
00:34:23,061 --> 00:34:25,897
(Matsuhiko) Oh? You think this junk is a legacy?

540
00:34:28,149 --> 00:34:33,404
For example, this piece is by a famous author⸺

541
00:34:33,488 --> 00:34:36,574
Currently, I think a market value of several million yen is worthless.

542
00:34:36,657 --> 00:34:37,950
Millions! ?

543
00:34:38,034 --> 00:34:39,160
(Tatsumi) Yes.

544
00:34:39,243 --> 00:34:43,539
There are also pieces that were actually used in shogi battles⸺

545
00:34:43,623 --> 00:34:46,918
There were also boxes with the autographs of the players who played against them.

546
00:34:48,211 --> 00:34:50,588
What was also interesting was⸺

547
00:34:50,671 --> 00:34:56,260
This is a locking move from a very old chess game.

548
00:34:56,344 --> 00:34:58,221
(Sugio) A similar seal⸺

549
00:34:58,304 --> 00:34:59,764
There are great prices on the auction site.

550
00:34:59,847 --> 00:35:00,723
(Matsuhiko) Huh?

551
00:35:00,807 --> 00:35:04,018
(Torataro) Probably while traveling around the country for the title match⸺

552
00:35:04,101 --> 00:35:06,187
I guess it was bought all over the place.

553
00:35:07,063 --> 00:35:08,940
(Shiori) Well, the chairman is⸺

554
00:35:09,023 --> 00:35:12,235
I didn't just live a life full of shogi...

555
00:35:12,318 --> 00:35:13,736
(Torataro) Better than everyone expected⸺

556
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:15,613
It may not be much, but⸺

557
00:35:16,322 --> 00:35:19,325
There was definitely a legacy.

558
00:35:19,951 --> 00:35:21,994
(Tatsumi) And that's not all.

559
00:35:22,078 --> 00:35:23,704
Tadayoshi has one more thing⸺

560
00:35:23,788 --> 00:35:26,582
You left an important message

561
00:35:26,666 --> 00:35:28,543
What is it? That's it

562
00:35:28,626 --> 00:35:31,295
In Tsume Shogi's will⸺

563
00:35:31,379 --> 00:35:33,506
Everyone's name was there.

564
00:35:33,589 --> 00:35:37,176
The player has 7 types of pieces, from foot to rook.

565
00:35:37,260 --> 00:35:38,261
 Tsume Shogi is⸺

566
00:35:38,344 --> 00:35:41,305
These are all rules that must be used.

567
00:35:41,389 --> 00:35:47,395
In other words, they have four children: Shiori, Yuma, and Okayama.

568
00:35:47,478 --> 00:35:50,231
I can't point out if any of these people are missing.

569
00:35:51,065 --> 00:35:52,859
(Torataro) Everyone while solving Tsume Shogi⸺

570
00:35:52,942 --> 00:35:58,155
We forgot about our heritage and worked together as one.

571
00:36:03,202 --> 00:36:06,789
That moment when everyone was passionate about Tsume Shogi⸺

572
00:36:07,957 --> 00:36:10,501
It was something that my father wanted to leave behind.

573
00:36:11,127 --> 00:36:12,545
Yeah

574
00:36:14,922 --> 00:36:18,843
I want us to come together and protect this house.

575
00:36:20,261 --> 00:36:24,891
That's the message my father really wanted to leave behind.

576
00:36:27,560 --> 00:36:31,731
What, are you asking me to play shogi now?

577
00:36:31,814 --> 00:36:33,858
Even though I used to tear my family apart by playing shogi.

578
00:36:33,941 --> 00:36:36,193
I'm surprised you love shogi so much.

579
00:36:36,277 --> 00:36:37,653
you guys are misunderstanding

580
00:36:38,404 --> 00:36:41,574
Dad is me, you and mom⸺

581
00:36:41,657 --> 00:36:44,327
He tried to connect with me by playing shogi.

582
00:36:52,543 --> 00:36:55,421
I was reminded of this when I saw this

583
00:36:58,007 --> 00:37:02,053
I also always misunderstood my father.

584
00:37:03,679 --> 00:37:07,934
I completely forgot that my mother loved shogi.

585
00:37:08,476 --> 00:37:10,978
(Matsuhiko) Is this photo us?

586
00:37:11,979 --> 00:37:14,023
(Shiko) Mom is playing shogi with us?

587
00:37:14,106 --> 00:37:19,320
My mother always liked shogi even before she got married.

588
00:37:19,403 --> 00:37:22,490
But I have no memory of playing shogi with my mom.

589
00:37:22,573 --> 00:37:24,450
Huh... I can't help it.

590
00:37:24,533 --> 00:37:29,246
At this time, Sugio was only 4 years old and Matsuhiko was 8 years old.

591
00:37:30,206 --> 00:37:34,293
To make matters worse, my mother was admitted to the hospital shortly after this.

592
00:37:36,754 --> 00:37:42,093
Now that I think about it, my mother didn't have much time left to live⸺

593
00:37:43,219 --> 00:37:45,179
Dad knew, right?

594
00:37:47,932 --> 00:37:49,642
surely…

595
00:37:49,725 --> 00:37:50,685
(Hiiragi) Thank you

596
00:37:50,768 --> 00:37:52,186
(Kirieda) That's why...

597
00:37:54,021 --> 00:37:58,275
(Hiiragi) What if you?

598
00:37:58,359 --> 00:38:01,779
When I couldn't come back from this hospitalization...

599
00:38:01,862 --> 00:38:05,658
Don't say anything more, you'll come back

600
00:38:07,785 --> 00:38:12,123
When I come back, I'll let you play shogi with those kids to your heart's content.

601
00:38:13,541 --> 00:38:15,668
Don't ever say you're not coming back

602
00:38:23,259 --> 00:38:26,429
(Torataro) The one who really liked shogi in this house was⸺

603
00:38:27,555 --> 00:38:29,140
It was your mother

604
00:38:32,935 --> 00:38:38,941
So my father tried to connect the four of us with my mother, who wasn't there.

605
00:38:39,942 --> 00:38:42,069
I want you to get better soon

606
00:38:42,153 --> 00:38:44,322
I hope so...

607
00:38:44,405 --> 00:38:45,239
You can't become stronger!

608
00:38:45,322 --> 00:38:48,409
(Kirieda) You treated us harshly.

609
00:38:49,327 --> 00:38:53,789
I'm really clumsy

610
00:38:55,833 --> 00:38:58,669
(Tatsumi) Shogi has the power to connect people.

611
00:38:59,962 --> 00:39:05,843
The person who believed in this more than anyone else was the late Tadayoshi.

612
00:39:10,014 --> 00:39:14,769
Come to think of it, it was a fatherly will.

613
00:39:17,229 --> 00:39:22,151
Mr. Kirie, as a representative of the heir⸺

614
00:39:23,319 --> 00:39:28,991
I hope that the inherited assets will be managed in accordance with Chairman Utsugi's will.

615
00:39:29,825 --> 00:39:31,118
Yeah

616
00:39:32,536 --> 00:39:34,705
This is a treasure left behind by my father.

617
00:39:35,373 --> 00:39:38,209
I won't let you easily exchange it for money.

618
00:39:39,710 --> 00:39:44,924
Shiori-san, Yuma-kun, and Okayama-san too⸺

619
00:39:45,007 --> 00:39:48,803
Please accept my father's wishes.

620
00:39:49,387 --> 00:39:52,389
Such wasteful words...

621
00:39:52,473 --> 00:39:54,100
thank you

622
00:39:55,559 --> 00:39:57,978
You guys are good too, right?

623
00:39:58,062 --> 00:40:01,357
Ah I understand

624
00:40:01,440 --> 00:40:03,692
I don't really mind though

625
00:40:03,776 --> 00:40:06,320
If my sister says so, I can't help it.

626
00:40:07,822 --> 00:40:11,700
How can I really express my gratitude to both of you?

627
00:40:11,784 --> 00:40:16,455
Oh, no, I was just doing my job as a lawyer.

628
00:40:16,956 --> 00:40:19,166
I'm glad I could help you

629
00:40:27,883 --> 00:40:31,011
It's not a battle of impressions, is it?

630
00:40:31,095 --> 00:40:35,516
Yes, this time it wasn't a court battle.

631
00:40:35,599 --> 00:40:38,978
Yes, then why?

632
00:40:40,646 --> 00:40:43,607
I wanted to try pointing at Kotaro-sensei once.

633
00:40:45,109 --> 00:40:46,152
Huh?

634
00:40:46,235 --> 00:40:47,194
(Tatsuo) Ever since that match⸺

635
00:40:47,403 --> 00:40:51,365
Tatsumi no longer plays shogi with anyone.

636
00:40:52,992 --> 00:40:54,243
Now, Kotaro-sensei's first turn.

637
00:40:54,326 --> 00:40:56,120
(Torataro) Oh yeah

638
00:40:57,913 --> 00:41:00,833
Thank you very much.

639
00:41:00,916 --> 00:41:02,376
please

640
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:04,461
♪～

641
00:41:18,184 --> 00:41:20,978
You can't play shogi without an opponent.

642
00:41:22,521 --> 00:41:25,524
Yes, that's right.

643
00:41:27,026 --> 00:41:31,280
(Tatsumi) I connect with others through shogi⸺

644
00:41:31,363 --> 00:41:34,074
And we can understand each other

645
00:41:35,034 --> 00:41:37,745
I love moments like that

646
00:41:39,205 --> 00:41:43,167
When I looked at the people in that house, I couldn't help but think that way.

647
00:41:43,959 --> 00:41:46,003
That's why I wanted to point it out.

648
00:41:52,051 --> 00:41:55,971
Ah... this this...

649
00:41:57,056 --> 00:41:58,891
King hand? Ah oh...

650
00:41:58,974 --> 00:42:00,643
…Or rather, it’s stuck?

651
00:42:00,726 --> 00:42:03,020
Yes, I'm stuck with 14 moves.

652
00:42:03,103 --> 00:42:03,938
Ah...

653
00:42:05,022 --> 00:42:07,399
Although it took longer than Yuma-kun⸺

654
00:42:08,234 --> 00:42:09,151
The drawer wins.

655
00:42:09,235 --> 00:42:11,028
Ah, no, no, no... wait a minute.

656
00:42:11,111 --> 00:42:12,905
Wait a minute, try again...

657
00:42:22,873 --> 00:42:26,418
Rie-san, not yet.

658
00:42:27,086 --> 00:42:29,630
You said you were only paid until yesterday.

659
00:42:29,713 --> 00:42:31,215
(Tatsumi) Hot spring shogi sweets⸺

660
00:42:31,298 --> 00:42:33,133
I was thinking of eating with you.

661
00:42:35,719 --> 00:42:37,471
 (Torataro) Let's wait a little bit.

662
00:42:37,554 --> 00:42:39,556
～♪

663
00:42:40,182 --> 00:42:42,142
 (door chime)

664
00:42:42,226 --> 00:42:43,727
Are you a customer? Ahhh

665
00:42:43,811 --> 00:42:46,313
Yes, welcome to Ayuda Law Office

666
00:42:46,939 --> 00:42:48,565
At least one is good.

667
00:42:49,316 --> 00:42:51,443
(Female) Attorney Tatsumi Tendo⸺

668
00:42:51,527 --> 00:42:52,945
Are you here?

669
00:42:53,445 --> 00:42:54,280
Yes

670
00:42:54,363 --> 00:42:56,574
Tatsumi Sensei Customer

671
00:42:56,657 --> 00:42:58,158
- (Tatsumi) Yeah? - (Torataro) Please

672
00:43:02,329 --> 00:43:03,330
 (sound of door closing)

673
00:43:05,874 --> 00:43:07,001
Usa-chan?

674
00:43:07,084 --> 00:43:08,294
What?

675
00:43:09,253 --> 00:43:12,840
(Usagiha) Long time no see, Dora

676
00:43:17,970 --> 00:43:20,097
(Tatsumi) The way I lost my friends⸺

677
00:43:20,180 --> 00:43:21,765
He still hasn't forgiven me for what I said.

678
00:43:21,849 --> 00:43:24,184
(Usagiba) Dora will accept it.

679
00:43:24,268 --> 00:43:25,894
Aren't you completely denying the contents of this article?

680
00:43:25,978 --> 00:43:26,812
 (Tsuge) This is not conclusive evidence.

681
00:43:26,895 --> 00:43:28,814
(Usagiba) This is all I have now

682
00:43:28,897 --> 00:43:29,898
You can't win this game

683
00:43:29,982 --> 00:43:31,775
(Rie) Mr. Torataro?

684
00:43:31,859 --> 00:43:32,860
Arrested!?
